    <p> This morning it should finally go to a German doctor for Steffi so that someone finally looks at their neck and what is against tension. </p>
    <p> When we woke up at the commuter parking lot this morning, it was so full that some vehicles had to park on the green strips. Since we also had something to do, we only quickly made McDonalds fresh. Then we made our way to the clinic. </p>
    <p> Once there, we were informed that the German -speaking doctor is now retired. We were then sent to the emergency room. There we were informed that it costs at least $ 450 if a doctor looks at Steffi's Genick. Uff. Steffi was then recommended by the nurse to eat paracetamol tablets for a few days and to strain the neck buttically but steadily. This was my favorite saying: "And to the left, to the right and now circle." We decided to stay in Melbourne for the next three nights and to see if it gets better. </p>
    <p> So we were faced with our favorite problem. Where to stay? Unfortunately, our camping guide didn't want to help us in Melbourne either. Spontaneously I just asked Google. There we only found campsites from <a title="&Ouml;ffnet Webseite von BIG4 in neuem Fenster" href="https://www.big4.com.au/" target="_blank"> Big4 </a> . This campsite chain has stumbled into my trip during the preparations for my trip. I immediately remembered that these places are extremely expensive. </p>
    <p> After even Google no other alternatives spit out, we had no choice but to see where a Big4 campsite is free in Melbourne and what it costs. </p>
