    <p> Then we found a place, a few km, northeast of the city center with the name <a title="&Ouml;ffnet Ashley Gardens im neuen Fenster" href="https://ashley-gardens.vic.big4.com.au/" target="_blank"> Ashley Gardens </a> . So call and ask if a place is free and what the fun should cost us. The friendly lady on the phone informed us that she has a place for 3 nights for us and that the fun costs us $ 42 a night. </p>
    <p> Since the selection was not large, we decided to go there. On the way there we stopped at a larger shopping center to stock up on fresh food for the next few days. There I convinced Steffi to finally choose her subsequent Christmas ghost. What she chose is not revealed here. Look in the next few days, just go in and take care of it. I am sure that it will appear in one or the other photo. </p>
    <p> When we arrived at the campsite in the early afternoon and signed up, we were picked up by a friendly gentleman in the golf kart at the entrance. In the convoy we drove over the not exactly large campsite to our parking space for the next three days. This parking space is extremely good. Directly opposite the washing house. With family bathroom directly in front of the van. Feels like your own bathroom. After the food stowed in the fridge, we went over the square for a short walk and promptly thread the big pool and the nice little sauna with a whirlpool. We decided to end the days comfortably and to lie down in/in the pool. See you in the morning. </p>
